JOHANNESBURG, November 16 – Two people died on Friday morning and another was seriously injured when three heavy motor vehicles were involved in a collision along the R103 Nottingham Road in Midlands, KwaZulu-Natal. Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said: “Sadly two occupants of one of the trucks had died and one occupant of another truck was left in a serious condition”. Herbst said the injured patient was treated on scene by an Advanced life support paramedic before being taken to a hospital. Authorities were on scene probing the cause of the fatal crash. – African News Agency (ANA)